20increase%2C%20attributed%20to%20temporary%20rotations%2C%20has%20been%20in%20effect%20for%20months%20and%20is%20unrelated%20to%20the%20recent%20fall%20of%20the%20Assad%20regime%20or%20increased%20ISIS%20activity%2C%20though%20it%20aims%20to%20counter%20the%20group.%20The%20move%20has%20prompted%20varied%20reactions%20from%20neighboring%20countries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftemporary-rotational-deployments-pentagon-confirms-doubling-troop-presence-in-syria-before-assads-fall%2Farticleshow%2F116487056.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftemporary-rotational-deployments-pentagon-confirms-doubling-troop-presence-in-syria-before-assads-fall%2Famp_articleshow%2F116487056.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftemporary-rotational-deployments-pentagon-confirms-doubling-troop-presence-in-syria-before-assads-fall%2Famp_articleshow%2F116487056.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pak%20Developing%20Missiles%20That%20Eventually%20Could%20Hit%20US%3A%20White%20House%20Official%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20White%20House%20official%20on%20Thursday%20said%20nuclear-armed%20Pakistan%20is%20developing%20long-range%20ballistic%20missile%20capabilities%20that%20eventually%20could%20allow%20it%20to%20strike%20targets%20well%20beyond%20South%20Asia%2C%20making%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Bemerging%20threat%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Jon%20Finer's%20surprise%20revelation%20underscored%20how%20far%20the%20once-close%20ties%20between%20Washington%20and%20Islamabad%20have%20deteriorated%20since%20the%202021%20U.S.%20troop%20withdrawal%20from%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20raised%20questions%20about%20whether%20Pakistan%20has%20shifted%20the%20objectives%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20ballistic%20missile%20programs%20long%20intended%20to%20counter%20those%20of%20India%2C%20the%20victor%20in%20three%20major%20wars%20they%20have%20fought%20since%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20for%20International%20Peace%2C%20Finer%20said%20Pakistan%20has%20pursued%20%26quot%3Bincreasingly%20sophisticated%20missile%20technology%2C%20from%20long-range%20ballistic%20missile%20systems%20to%20equipment%2C%20that%20would%20enable%20the%20testing%20of%20significantly%20larger%20rocket%20motors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20those%20trends%20continue%2C%20Finer%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPakistan%20will%20have%20the%20capability%20to%20strike%20targets%20well%20beyond%20South%20Asia%2C%20including%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20nuclear-armed%20states%20with%20missiles%20that%20can%20reach%20the%20U.S.%20homeland%20%26quot%3Bis%20very%20small%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20adversarial%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%2C%20naming%20Russia%2C%20North%20Korea%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20candidly%2C%20it's%20hard%20for%20us%20to%20see%20Pakistan's%20actions%20as%20anything%20other%20than%20an%20emerging%20threat%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Finer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20speech%20came%20a%20day%20after%20Washington%20announced%20a%20new%20round%20of%20sanctions%20related%20to%20Pakistan's%20ballistic%20missile%20development%20program%2C%20including%20for%20the%20first%20time%20against%20the%20state-run%20defense%20agency%20that%20oversees%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistani%20embassy%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIslamabad%20casts%20its%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20ballistic%20missile%20programs%20as%20deterrents%20against%20Indian%20aggression%20and%20intended%20to%20maintain%20regional%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20senior%20administration%20officials%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20that%20the%20U.S.%20concerns%20with%20Pakistan's%20missile%20program%20have%20been%20long-standing%20and%20stemmed%20from%20the%20sizes%20of%20the%20rocket%20engines%20being%20developed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20threat%20posed%20to%20the%20United%20States%20is%20up%20to%20a%20decade%20away%2C%20said%20one%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiner's%20comments%2C%20the%20officials%20said%2C%20were%20intended%20to%20press%20Pakistani%20officials%20to%20address%20why%20they%20are%20developing%20more%20powerful%20rocket%20engines%2C%20something%20they%20have%20refused%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20acknowledge%20our%20concerns.%20They%20tell%20us%20we%20are%20biased%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20second%20U.S.%20official%2C%20adding%20that%20Pakistani%20officials%20have%20wrongly%20implied%20that%20U.S.%20sanctions%20on%20their%20missile%20program%20are%20intended%20%26quot%3Bto%20handicap%20their%20ability%20to%20defend%20against%20India.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiner%20included%20himself%20among%20senior%20U.S.%20officials%20who%20he%20said%20repeatedly%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20missile%20program%20with%20top%20Pakistani%20officials%20to%20no%20avail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWashington%20and%20Islamabad%2C%20he%20noted%2C%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Blong-time%20partners%26quot%3B%20on%20development%2C%20counter-terrorism%20and%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20makes%20us%20question%20even%20more%20why%20Pakistan%20will%20be%20motivated%20to%20develop%20a%20capability%20that%20could%20be%20used%20against%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20warm%20ties%20U.S.%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20has%20forged%20with%20its%20long-time%20foe%20India%2C%20and%20maintains%20close%20ties%20with%20China.%20Some%20Chinese%20entities%20have%20been%20slapped%20with%20U.S.%20sanctions%20for%20supplying%20Islamabad's%20ballistic%20missile%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20conducted%20its%20first%20nuclear%20weapons%20test%20in%201998%20-%20more%20than%2020%20years%20after%20India's%20first%20test%20blast%20-%20and%20has%20built%20an%20extensive%20arsenal%20of%20ballistic%20missiles%20capable%20of%20lofting%20nuclear%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bulletin%20of%20the%20American%20Scientists%20research%20organization%20estimates%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20a%20stockpile%20of%20about%20170%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.-Pakistani%20relations%20have%20undergone%20major%20ups%20and%20downs%2C%20including%20close%20Cold%20War%20ties%20that%20saw%20them%20support%20Afghan%20rebels%20against%20the%201979-89%20Soviet%20occupation%20of%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20also%20was%20a%20key%20partner%20in%20the%20U.S.%20fight%20against%20al%20Qaeda%20following%20the%20Sept.%2011%2C%202001%2C%20attacks%20on%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20has%20been%20a%20major%20non-NATO%20ally%20since%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20ties%20also%20have%20been%20hurt%20by%20coups%20staged%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20military%2C%20its%20support%20for%20the%20Taliban's%201996-2001%20rule%20and%20its%20nuclear%20weapons%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20experts%20said%20Finer's%20speech%20came%20as%20a%20major%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20senior%20U.S.%20official%20to%20publicly%20link%20concerns%20about%20proliferation%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20a%20future%20direct%20threat%20to%20the%20U.S.%20homeland%20-%20this%20is%20a%20mighty%20dramatic%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20Kugelman%20of%20the%20Wilson%20Center%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734667800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-1