%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2ldj04p0q2o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2ldj04p0q2o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20scientist%20working%20to%20create%20'mirror%20life'%20discovered%20it%20could%20be%20'a%20perfect%20bioweapon.'%20She's%20asking%20other%20researchers%20to%20stop.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223750%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22orange%20microscope%20view%20of%20a%20cell%20dividing%20in%20a%20webby%20matrix%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6764c23b1cee543535a86ea8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMirror%20cells%2C%20if%20created%2C%20would%20probably%20multiply%20in%20a%20host%20organism%20without%20much%20resistance.%3Cp%3EBSIP%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20scientists%20trying%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Bmirror%20life%26quot%3B%20have%20stopped%20in%20their%20tracks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20mirror%20microorganism%20could%20end%20up%20being%20a%20major%20pathogen%20since%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fomicron-may-build-superimmunity-for-future-coronavirus-variants-2022-1%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmune%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20wouldn't%20notice%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMirror-image%20biology%20inverts%20a%20fundamental%20property%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%3A%20which%20way%20molecules%20point.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20%26quot%3Bmirror%20life%26quot%3B%20could%20be%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuperconductors-nuclear-fusion-need-chatgpt-moment-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escience's%20greatest%20breakthroughs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20some%20researchers%20who%20began%20the%20effort%20are%20now%20calling%20for%20it%20to%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20mirror-life%20microorganisms%20exist%20yet.%20However%2C%2038%20scientists%20warned%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.ads9158%23body-ref-R15%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Science%20on%20December%2012%20that%20if%20someone%20created%20one%20and%20it%20escaped%20the%20lab%2C%20it%20could%20cause%20a%20catastrophic%20multi-species%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-real-is-the-last-of-us-science-behind-fungus-pandemic-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epandemic%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20basically%20giving%20instructions%20of%20how%20to%20make%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-probably-wont-create-biological-weapons-threats-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperfect%20bioweapon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Kate%20Adamala%2C%20a%20co-author%20of%20the%20paper%20and%20a%20chemist%20who%20leads%20a%20synthetic%20biology%20lab%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20risks%20became%20clear%2C%20Adamala%20ended%20her%20lab's%20efforts%20toward%20building%20a%20mirror%20cell.%20Her%20multi-year%20grant%20for%20that%20facet%20of%20their%20research%20expired%20and%20she%20decided%20not%20to%20apply%20for%20renewal%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20she's%20urging%20other%20scientists%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20along%20with%20the%2037%20other%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20we%20were%20initially%20skeptical%20that%20mirror%20bacteria%20could%20pose%20major%20risks%2C%20we%20have%20become%20deeply%20concerned%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote%20in%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207175118-4d4e-47ba-80cc-01e6d6ac5017%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20mirror%20life%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMirror%20biology%20takes%20a%20fundamental%20rule%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%20called%20chirality%2C%20and%20flips%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChirality%20is%20the%20simple%20fact%20that%20molecules%20%E2%80%94%20like%20sugars%20and%20amino%20acids%20%E2%80%94%20point%20in%20one%20of%20two%20directions.%20They%20are%20either%20right-handed%20or%20left-handed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20reason%2C%20though%2C%20life%20will%20only%20use%20one%20chiral%20form%20of%20each%20molecule.%20DNA%2C%20for%20example%2C%20only%20uses%20right-handed%20sugars%20for%20its%20backbone.%20That's%20why%20it%20twists%20to%20the%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20mirror%20biology%2C%20scientists%20aim%20to%20create%20living%20cells%20where%20all%20the%20chirality%20is%20flipped.%20Where%20natural%20life%20uses%20a%20right-handed%20peptide%2C%20to%20build%20proteins%2C%20mirror%20life%20would%20use%20the%20same%20peptide%20in%20its%20left-handed%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdamala's%20research%20was%20focused%20on%20making%20mirror%20peptides%2C%20which%20can%20help%20create%20longer-lasting%20pharmaceuticals.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20full%20mirror%20cell%20was%20the%20long-term%20goal%20of%20that%20research.%20Mirror%20cells%20could%20help%20prevent%20contamination%20in%20bioreactors%20that%20use%20bacteria%20for%20green%20chemical%20manufacturing%20because%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20interact%20with%20natural%20microorganisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20have%20this%20perfect%20bioreactor%20that%20can%20just%20sit%20there%20and%20you%20can%20stick%20your%20finger%20into%20it%20and%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20contaminate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Adamala%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20also%20precisely%20the%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mirror%20bacteria%20could%20bypass%20the%20natural%20checks%20and%20balances%20of%20life%2C%20like%20competing%20with%20other%20bacteria%20or%20battling%20our%20immune%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bac12f88-5bf0-463b-85b1-5f7bea32e792%5C%22%3EImmune%20systems%20would%20ignore%20mirror%20cells%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdamala%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20death%20sentence%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20mirror-cell%20research%20came%20when%20she%20spoke%20to%20immunologists.%20They%20explained%20that%20for%20humans%2C%20other%20animals%2C%20and%20plants%2C%20immune%20system%20activation%20depends%20on%20chirality.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImmune%20cells%20recognize%20pathogens'%20proteins%2C%20but%20they%20wouldn't%20detect%20the%20inverse%20versions%20of%20those%20proteins%20that%20mirror%20cells%20would%20use.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mirror%20pathogen%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20interact%20with%20the%20host.%20It%20just%20uses%20it%20as%20a%20warm%20incubator%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20nutrients%2C%26quot%3B%20Adamala%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20mirror%20bacteria%20escaped%20the%20lab%2C%20it%20could%20cause%20slow%2C%20persistent%20infections%20that%20can't%20be%20treated%20with%20antibiotics%20(because%20those%2C%20too%2C%20rely%20on%20chirality).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20they%20wouldn't%20face%20any%20immune%20resistance%2C%20mirror%20bacteria%20wouldn't%20need%20to%20specialize%20in%20infecting%20corn%2C%20or%20goats%2C%20or%20birds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20a%20disease%20of%20anything%20that%20lives%20that%20can%20be%20infected%2C%26quot%3B%20Adamala%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20a%20mirror%20bacteria%20would%20multiply%20endlessly%2C%20unfettered.%20It%20would%20take%20over%20its%20hosts%20and%20eventually%20kill%20them.%20It%20would%20destroy%20crops.%20It%20would%20have%20no%20predators.%20It%20would%20overwhelm%20entire%20ecosystems%2C%20swapping%20out%20portions%20of%20our%20natural%20world%20for%20a%20new%20mirror%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5b3f3fd-1f38-403c-a5be-35890417b185%5C%22%3EA%20long%20way%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETing%20Zhu%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20researchers%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20mirror%20cell%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email%20that%20he%20supports%20being%20cautious%20but%20doesn't%20think%20%26quot%3Ba%20complete%20mirror-image%20bacterium%20can%20be%20synthesized%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhu%20leads%20a%20mirror-image%20biology%20lab%20at%20Westlake%20University%20in%20China.%20He%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20Science%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdamala%20estimates%20that%20the%20world's%20first%20mirror%20bacteria%20is%20still%20about%20a%20decade%20away.%20She%20argues%20that's%20exactly%20why%20the%20research%20should%20stop%20now%20before%20it%20builds%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20someone%20could%20use%20to%20make%20that%20final%20leap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20can%20do%20it%20on%20their%20own%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Adamala%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20technology%20is%20not%20mature%20enough%2C%20which%20means%20we're%20pretty%20well%20safeguarded%20against%20someone%20crazy%20enough%20to%20say%2C%20'I'll%20just%20go%20do%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Adamala%20and%20the%20other%20paper%20authors%20invited%20more%20research%20and%20scrutiny%20on%20the%20risks%20they've%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20does%20prove%20us%20wrong%2C%20that%20would%20make%20me%20really%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmirror-life-biology-research-risks-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734658610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6764c2681cee543535a86eb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmirror-life-biology-research-risks-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22No%20mirror-image%20life%20exists%20yet%2C%20but%20scientists%20are%20calling%20for%20the%20research%20to%20stop%20before%20it%20gets%20close%20to%20a%20breakthrough.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%