ds%20it%20to%20the%20US%20Congress%20which%20then%20examines%20it%20thoroughly.%20The%20Pentagon%20keeps%20a%20very%20close%20watch%20on%20China's%20military%20activities%20and%20tracks%20its%20progress%20on%20various%20parameters%20on%20a%20yearly%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20report%20has%20revealed%20something%20startling%20about%20China's%20nuclear%20weapons%20stockpile.%20In%20an%20era%20where%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20world%20is%20on%20de-nuclearisation%20and%20disarmament%2C%20Beijing%20was%20found%20to%20most-actively%20adding%20weapons%20to%20its%20stockpile.%20At%20least%20100%20nuclear%20warheads%20have%20been%20added%20to%20its%20arsenal%20in%202024%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FSpotlights%2F2024-China-Military-Power-Report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPentagon%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20highlights%20that%20China%20now%20looks%20to%20accelerate%20the%20pace%20of%20producing%20even%20more%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20cross%20the%201%2C000-nukes%20mark%20by%202030.%20It%20is%20estimated%20that%20China%20currently%20has%20around%20600%20nukes%20in%20its%20inventory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20has%20the%20world's%20leading%20hypersonic%20missile%20arsenal%20and%20has%20advanced%20its%20development%20of%20both%20conventional%20and%20nuclear-armed%20hypersonic%20missile%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20stated.%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20China%20will%20continue%20to%20grow%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20at%20least%20till%202035.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20POLICY%20OF%20SECRECY%20AND%20DECEIT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20keeps%20everything%20related%20to%20its%20military%20and%20defence%20a%20closely-guarded%20secret.%20It%20never%20divulges%20any%20information%20regarding%20its%20army%2C%20air%20force%2C%20or%20navy%2C%20and%20the%20weapons%20under%20their%20control.%20Though%20Beijing%20formally%20announces%20a%20defence%20budget%20annually%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20believes%20that%20is%20not%20the%20true%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Beijing%20announced%20an%20annual%20defence%20outlay%20of%20%24224%20billion%2C%20but%20Pentagon's%20report%20reveals%20China%20has%20spends%20at%20least%2040%20per%20cent%20more%20than%20what%20it%20officially%20declares.%20This%20brings%20the%20defence%20budget%20anywhere%20in%20the%20range%20of%20%24350%20billion%20to%20%24450%20billion%20-%20or%20roughly%20half%20the%20US%20defence%20budget%2C%20which%20is%20over%20%24880%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPentagon's%20research%20also%20highlights%20Beijing's%20wider%20focus%20to%20further%20modernise%20its%20military%20by%20developing%20a%20range%20of%20new%20missiles%2C%20including%20Intercontinental%20Ballistic%20Missiles%20or%20ICBMs%20-%20both%20conventional%20and%20nuclear%20-%20%26quot%3Bthat%20could%20strike%20Alaska%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20and%20the%20continental%20United%20States%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Navy%20is%20already%20the%20largest%20in%20the%20world%20with%20a%20declared%20fleet%20size%20of%20more%20than%20370%20ships%20and%20submarines.%20This%20is%20significantly%20larger%20than%20the%20fleet%20size%20of%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20which%20is%20290%20ships%20and%20submarines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20air%20force%20too%20is%20a%20force%20to%20be%20reckoned%20with%20as%20it%20has%20more%20than%201%2C200%20fighter%20jets%20that%20are%20fourth-generation%20military%20aircraft%20-%20at%20par%20with%20some%20of%20the%20most%20sophisticated%20fighter%20jets%20manufactured%20by%20the%20United%20States%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20Europe.%20China's%20air%20force%20has%20an%20overall%20strength%20close%20to%202%2C000%20aircraft%2C%20which%20is%20massive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS-CHINA%20DEFENCE%20TIES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20there%20is%20a%20basic%20structure%20for%20defence%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20nations%2C%20and%20communication%20does%20take%20place%20at%20a%20junior%20level%2C%20China%20has%20rejected%20any%20high-level%20dialogue%20or%20cooperation%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20US%20Secretary%20of%20Defence%20Lloyd%20Austin%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Chinese%20Defence%20Minister%20Dong%20Jun%20for%20a%20meeting%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20defence%20summit%20in%20Laos%20last%20month%2C%20the%20latter%20declined%20it.%20Secretary%20Austin%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bunfortunate%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20such%20an%20attitude%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bsetback%20for%20the%20entire%20region%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncoming%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20appointed%20two%20fierce%20China%20hawks%20in%20his%20administration%20-%20Marco%20Rubio%20as%20the%20Secretary%20of%20State%20and%20Mike%20Walz%20as%20the%20US%20National%20Security%20Adviser.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ethe%20Chinese%20government%20has%20placed%20sanctions%20on%20Marco%20Rubio%2C%20and%20in%202020%20had%20banned%20him%20from%20ever%20entering%20the%20country%20again%20-%20something%20Beijing%20would%20need%20to%20reconsider%20when%20he%20takes%20office%20as%20Secretary%20of%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeeks%20before%20the%20Trump%20Administration%20takes%20over%2C%20NSA-designate%20Mike%20Waltz%20has%20already%20urged%20President-elect%20Trump%20to%20%26quot%3Burgently%20end%20the%20conflicts%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20in%20order%20to%20counter%20the%20greater%20threat%20from%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%26quot%3B.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734637200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fano10vv_china-nuclear-weapons-_625x300_18_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpentagons-china-report-has-a-startling-revelation-about-its-nuclear-weapons-7289103%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Every%20year%20the%20Pentagon%20prepares%20a%20detailed%20spe